WEBVTT

00:52.030 --> 00:57.030
<font color="#ffff00">Provided by explosiveskull</font>
https://twitter.com/kaboomskull

01:03.665 --> 01:05.432
<i>I never believed in fate</i>

01:06.000 --> 01:09.904
<i>or destiny, kismet,
whatever you want to call it.</i>

01:11.739 --> 01:16.443
<i>Never believed in Santa,
magic, even as a kid.</i>

01:17.411 --> 01:18.613
<i>The supernatural.</i>

01:19.847 --> 01:21.949
<i>God, heaven, hell.</i>

01:23.250 --> 01:23.951
<i>No.</i>

01:27.354 --> 01:29.322
<i>I never believed
in anything really.</i>

01:32.259 --> 01:33.527
<i>And then I met Floyd.</i>

01:38.900 --> 01:41.435
Let's talk about that
for a moment, Sam, if we could.

01:42.036 --> 01:44.304
I believe that's chapter...

01:45.707 --> 01:47.642
Yes, chapter three
from the book.

01:51.578 --> 01:54.381
I don't remember much
of the night I met Floyd.

01:56.450 --> 01:58.552
I remember
that I was intoxicated

01:58.853 --> 02:02.522
and had been since
around 1:30 that afternoon.

02:03.423 --> 02:04.926
Fuck.

02:04.959 --> 02:07.294
<i>I remember that
I couldn't pay my rent again</i>

02:07.561 --> 02:09.731
<i>and that I hadn't paid it
for five months.</i>

02:09.764 --> 02:11.666
It's all over everywhere!

02:11.699 --> 02:15.268
<i>I remember that it had been
a year since Kathleen dumped me.</i>

02:16.804 --> 02:18.840
<i>Almost two since my mother died.</i>

02:21.676 --> 02:25.378
<i>And everything felt incrementally
shittier with each passing day.</i>

02:25.412 --> 02:27.915
Fuck!

02:27.949 --> 02:31.284
<i>And I remember that I took
a brief mental inventory,</i>

02:31.619 --> 02:34.254
<i>considered my overwhelming
lack of prospects,</i>

02:34.756 --> 02:37.257
and in my state
of absolute crapulance...

02:38.592 --> 02:40.527
...came to the superb
conclusion that...

02:43.664 --> 02:45.066
...that it's time to go.

07:26.013 --> 07:28.315
Shit.

07:29.083 --> 07:30.351
Oh, fuck!

07:30.384 --> 07:32.119
Oh, shit.

07:41.062 --> 07:41.962
Oh, shit.

08:01.916 --> 08:03.384
Okay, okay.

08:03.417 --> 08:04.885
Hey, hey, hey.

08:04.919 --> 08:06.921
Hey, okay. Hey. Look at me.

08:06.954 --> 08:09.256
Hey, hey. Hey, son, son.

08:09.290 --> 08:11.225
There's been an accident.
But you look fine.

08:11.258 --> 08:12.293
Everything's fine.

08:15.696 --> 08:16.897
Oh, fuck.

08:19.033 --> 08:20.167
Oh, shit.

08:25.906 --> 08:28.375
Stay with me.
Stay with me. Shit.

08:29.009 --> 08:31.045
Stay with me.

08:33.881 --> 08:37.118
God, God!

08:37.451 --> 08:39.120
God!

10:52.920 --> 10:55.256
<i>It's a goddamn
miracle that the kid's alive.</i>

10:55.889 --> 10:57.958
<i>I would have to say "miraculous"</i>

10:57.992 --> 10:59.927
<i>is the only adequate
description.</i>

11:00.461 --> 11:02.863
<i>So aside from the
bum wrist and the, uh,</i>

11:02.896 --> 11:05.366
- <i>broken ribs.</i>
- <i>Well, there was the associated puncture</i>

11:05.399 --> 11:07.067
<i>of the right lung, of course.</i>

11:07.101 --> 11:08.535
<i>The perforation of the bladder.</i>

11:09.903 --> 11:11.805
- <i>Uh, the bladder is functioning quite well now.</i>
- <i>Hmm.</i>

11:12.439 --> 11:15.309
So he won't need, uh,
diapers or anything

11:15.876 --> 11:17.911
- permanently?
- No, he will not.

11:21.515 --> 11:22.783
Can you smoke in here?

11:24.051 --> 11:25.252
I'm afraid you can't.

11:28.122 --> 11:31.859
He exited the coma at
approximately 9:15 last night.

11:32.593 --> 11:36.930
His last recollection is being in
the city on the day of the accident.

11:37.298 --> 11:43.003
He's lucid, communicative if not somewhat
despondent, which is to be expected.

11:43.470 --> 11:46.106
He will recover.
But I should tell you

11:46.140 --> 11:48.542
that there may be some
hurdles in the near term.

11:50.144 --> 11:51.412
What kind of hurdles?

11:51.445 --> 11:53.615
Oh, he may experience
mood swings,

11:53.648 --> 11:56.850
agitation, occasional confusion,
but, uh...

11:58.352 --> 12:00.054
...that should
dissipate with time.

12:05.959 --> 12:06.860
The brain.

12:08.262 --> 12:10.230
The brain is an incredible
instrument, Floyd,

12:11.365 --> 12:13.635
capable of the most
amazing things.

12:13.668 --> 12:17.371
But for all of its tremendous
power and magnificence,

12:18.038 --> 12:22.543
it is incredibly fragile
and remarkably sensitive.

12:23.277 --> 12:27.848
<i>And miracles aside, with all the
trauma that Samuel has suffered,</i>

12:28.382 --> 12:31.185
<i>it may be some time before
his faculties come back to him.</i>

12:32.052 --> 12:35.889
<i>Truth be told, he may never be
that Samuel again.</i>

12:56.043 --> 12:56.944
How are you doing?

13:04.551 --> 13:05.452
Who are you?

13:08.188 --> 13:09.156
The guy?

13:10.457 --> 13:11.358
My name's Floyd.

13:14.361 --> 13:15.262
Hey.

13:20.367 --> 13:22.035
I guess I should put these
in some water.

13:27.709 --> 13:30.511
You know, a lot of people out
there might frown upon a man

13:30.544 --> 13:32.246
giving another man
some flowers, but...

13:33.815 --> 13:37.151
...you don't have to worry about it.
I'm not sweet on men, nothing like that.

13:38.986 --> 13:40.187
I'm a family man.

13:42.489 --> 13:46.593
And I can assure you that I am definitely a fan of the dames.

13:47.161 --> 13:50.998
So, uh, Sammy,
please accept these flowers.

13:51.031 --> 13:53.200
- Please don't call me that.
- Call you what?

13:54.301 --> 13:57.404
Sammy. Don't call me Sammy.

13:57.438 --> 14:00.474
Sammy? Sammy is one of the greatest
nicknames in the history of mankind.

14:00.507 --> 14:03.143
- Hands down.
- Nobody calls me that.

14:03.177 --> 14:05.479
I prefer Samuel or...

14:07.448 --> 14:08.348
...Sam.

14:11.351 --> 14:12.486
Well, let's go with Sam.

14:13.520 --> 14:14.955
Thank you.

14:16.190 --> 14:18.358
- You really don't like Sammy?
- No, I really don't like it.

14:18.760 --> 14:20.561
Okay.
It's no problem.

14:20.594 --> 14:21.528
I'll call you Sam.

14:29.036 --> 14:34.074
You know, I've been, uh, here quite
a bit since the accident and, uh...

14:35.175 --> 14:36.076
Uh...

14:42.717 --> 14:43.685
I'm sorry I hit you.

14:49.056 --> 14:50.123
It just kind of happened.

14:52.627 --> 14:57.297
I still don't know what...
How... What...

15:03.170 --> 15:05.607
I'm just... I'm just... I'm just
sorry that I... that I hit you.

15:08.810 --> 15:10.210
It's fine. I'm fine.

15:11.411 --> 15:12.714
I'm here, uh...

15:14.147 --> 15:17.084
Besides, I don't remember any of
it, and it could have been worse.

15:17.117 --> 15:19.319
Yeah. Could have been worse.

15:26.393 --> 15:29.631
They said that your father
has not come to this...

15:29.664 --> 15:31.198
I... I don't want
to talk about it.

15:32.332 --> 15:34.535
Okay, I understand.

15:41.408 --> 15:44.211
Dr. Ike told me
that you were a writer.

15:48.448 --> 15:51.084
So I've been thinking, uh...

15:55.289 --> 15:57.190
...Would you consider
writing my biography?

15:59.259 --> 16:01.829
Uh, I don't...

16:03.163 --> 16:04.565
I'm not really, uh...

16:08.201 --> 16:13.140
I mean, thank you for thinking of
me, but I write short stories mostly.

16:13.173 --> 16:17.411
The occasionally essay,
a few poems. Biography?

16:18.613 --> 16:20.080
So you don't think
you can do it?

16:20.581 --> 16:23.383
It's not that I can't do it.
Of course I can do it.

16:23.417 --> 16:25.152
I'm capable. It's just...

16:26.186 --> 16:29.624
It's not my thing, Floyd.

16:30.591 --> 16:32.492
No, I understand, you're
an artist. I respect that.

16:32.526 --> 16:34.294
I can... I can see it
and I can feel it.

16:34.561 --> 16:35.596
But I challenge you.

16:36.965 --> 16:43.503
I challenge you to at least try
for once to do something different.

16:44.438 --> 16:47.642
Because when opportunity knocks on
your door, you might want to answer it,

16:47.909 --> 16:50.243
even if she's
wearing a goofy hat.

16:50.678 --> 16:53.246
- Huh?
- Just hear me out. I spoke to Dr. Ike,

16:53.280 --> 16:55.282
and he explained to me
the situation

16:55.315 --> 16:56.884
you're in with your landlord
in the city.

16:56.918 --> 16:58.686
- Why is he telling you all this?
- No, no, listen,

16:58.720 --> 17:00.454
there's nothing
to be embarrassed about.

17:00.487 --> 17:02.422
Everybody skips out
on their rent every so often.

17:02.690 --> 17:08.194
It's nothing. What I'm proposing is
that you come and stay with us out here,

17:08.228 --> 17:11.633
me and my family, until you get
yourself back on your feet.

17:12.265 --> 17:17.270
I can give you a cash stipend or a cash advance
if you want to get professional about it.

17:17.304 --> 17:20.907
And... and all you have to do is
concentrate on... on healing up, man.

17:21.575 --> 17:25.278
Just heal up
and write at your own pace.

17:25.311 --> 17:28.816
No deadlines. Just as it comes.

17:29.984 --> 17:31.585
How much of a cash stipend
are we talking?

17:31.619 --> 17:34.689
- How much do you want?
- Uh... um...

17:35.790 --> 17:37.190
Five hundred.

17:37.224 --> 17:38.258
- Five hundred it is.
- Per week.

17:38.291 --> 17:39.292
Dollars?

17:40.227 --> 17:42.262
What do you think I meant?

17:43.430 --> 17:44.699
I know what you meant.

17:50.738 --> 17:53.473
This might sound strange, but...

17:55.342 --> 17:57.411
...I have this funny
feeling that...

17:57.945 --> 18:02.582
<i>He paused for a moment,
pondering it, reconciling.</i>

18:03.450 --> 18:05.185
<i>Before finally admitting</i>

18:05.953 --> 18:07.521
<i>this was meant to be.</i>

18:09.556 --> 18:12.627
I repeated it to myself
in my head several times.

18:13.460 --> 18:19.599
"This was meant to be, this was
meant to be, this was meant to be."

18:20.300 --> 18:22.502
And wondered for just a moment

18:23.004 --> 18:26.406
if there was any possibility
he could be right.

19:09.851 --> 19:10.785
This is it.

19:12.820 --> 19:13.988
Beautiful home, Floyd.

19:16.323 --> 19:17.625
She really is, isn't she?

19:20.628 --> 19:21.796
Come on, let's go meet the kid.

19:24.632 --> 19:26.500
Hey, you all right, pal?

19:29.904 --> 19:30.805
Yeah.

19:32.774 --> 19:33.908
Come on, I'll get your stuff.

19:36.744 --> 19:38.780
Aloha. We're here.

19:40.547 --> 19:42.016
I got that.
Here, take a load off.

19:46.087 --> 19:49.657
Where's the goddamn welcoming committee, Jackie?

19:50.091 --> 19:50.992
Coming.

20:10.711 --> 20:13.346
<i>Jacqueline, Floyd's second wife.</i>

20:13.380 --> 20:15.448
<i>And over a quarter century
his junior.</i>

20:17.018 --> 20:19.921
<i>She was a successful attorney,
and on the partnership track</i>

20:19.954 --> 20:22.089
<i>at Hutchinson,
Zimmer, Wallerstein,</i>

20:22.123 --> 20:23.925
<i>Wallerstein, Cohen and Clemens.</i>

20:25.993 --> 20:28.830
<i>She loved the city,
hated the long commute.</i>

20:28.863 --> 20:30.597
<i>Would often work very late.</i>

20:30.631 --> 20:33.000
<i>She claimed to let the traffic
simmer down.</i>

20:36.671 --> 20:39.807
- Here's my boy, Eddie.
- Edward.

20:42.475 --> 20:43.978
<i>He reminded me of myself.</i>

20:51.551 --> 20:55.957
<i>He was a freshman at St.
Gerard Academy, the youngest in his class.</i>

20:55.990 --> 21:00.828
<i>A dangerous combination of incredible
precociousness and hardwired pessimism.</i>

21:02.096 --> 21:06.433
<i>His penchant for mischief hadn't yet
become a serious cause for concern</i>

21:06.466 --> 21:07.902
<i>between Floyd and Jacqueline.</i>

21:08.669 --> 21:10.771
<i>And though he didn't have
many friends.</i>

21:10.805 --> 21:13.074
<i>He seemed perfectly content
with the fact,</i>

21:13.841 --> 21:17.712
<i>as he said, "People are scared
of me and I like it."</i>

21:21.782 --> 21:25.720
Lily, can you do us a damn kindness
and come downstairs, please?

21:44.872 --> 21:47.608
<i>Lily was Floyd's daughter
from his first marriage.</i>

21:49.210 --> 21:52.479
<i>After graduating from
the music school at Fair Gate,</i>

21:52.512 --> 21:56.183
<i>she experienced a great deal of
difficulty pursuing a legitimate career</i>

21:56.217 --> 21:57.450
<i>as a violinist.</i>

22:04.725 --> 22:09.196
<i>Her growing sorrow helped turn occasional
drinking into frequent cocaine use.</i>

22:09.630 --> 22:13.000
<i>And this culminated in the
inevitable mini breakdown...</i>

22:14.501 --> 22:17.605
<i>...and requisite move back home
to reorganize.</i>

22:22.777 --> 22:23.945
Welcome to the family.

22:25.279 --> 22:29.016
Thank you so, so much.

22:34.288 --> 22:35.455
Very good.

22:58.746 --> 23:03.117
Uh, excuse me, but why
is my silverware so small?

23:05.286 --> 23:08.022
- How do you mean?
- Look, my fork, it's half...

23:10.057 --> 23:10.958
Uh.

23:12.126 --> 23:16.263
It...

23:16.897 --> 23:22.203
I'm... I'm sorry, I didn't, I didn't mean
smaller, I jus... I just meant I, uh...

23:22.937 --> 23:24.071
I meant.

23:26.573 --> 23:28.676
I me... Water.

23:33.314 --> 23:35.515
- Looks delicious, Gloria.
- <i>Gracias.</i>

23:38.085 --> 23:39.754
- You're good?
- Yeah.

23:40.621 --> 23:41.822
Okay, everybody, <i>Mangia</i>.

23:44.058 --> 23:48.729
So, Samuel, Floyd tells me that the two
of you are working together on a book.

23:49.830 --> 23:51.065
How exciting.

23:51.832 --> 23:53.667
I have no idea

23:53.701 --> 23:56.604
what it's about because he won't
give me any details, but...

23:57.271 --> 24:02.575
...I am sure it's going to be
just... sensational.

24:03.077 --> 24:04.779
- It's a secret.
- Mm.

24:05.146 --> 24:09.750
- Is it?
- Mm-hmm. Classified. For now.

24:12.386 --> 24:14.922
May I use the powder room?

24:14.955 --> 24:17.691
- Yes, uh, it's right down the hallway.
- Thank you.

24:17.725 --> 24:20.194
- It's to the... to the left.
- Okay, left.

24:24.732 --> 24:25.699
Dad.

24:25.733 --> 24:27.735
- Mm-hmm?
- Is he okay?

24:27.768 --> 24:28.702
Mm-hmm.

24:29.670 --> 24:32.206
He's fine. Just a little
shaken up, you know,

24:32.973 --> 24:36.911
from the, uh, accident.
Otherwise, he's fine.

24:38.979 --> 24:40.214
Pass the cheese.

24:58.099 --> 24:59.300
Rabbit.

25:24.859 --> 25:26.894
- Hey, hey, hey.
- What?

25:27.928 --> 25:30.030
- What fuck is that?
- The fuck's what?

25:32.466 --> 25:33.667
Is that a dead rabbit?

25:35.169 --> 25:36.904
Yeah, pretty much.

25:38.339 --> 25:40.207
Jesus fucking Christ. Well, will you...
will you please go back outside

25:40.241 --> 25:41.642
and bury that little fellow?

25:42.076 --> 25:45.813
- Hey, you been smoking again?
- Yep.

25:48.449 --> 25:51.085
You... you gotta quit smoking, man.
That shit's going to kill you.

25:51.118 --> 25:53.821
You're gonna end up like pops.
You want to end up like pops?

25:53.854 --> 25:54.755
Yep.

26:16.510 --> 26:17.945
Just a second.

26:19.480 --> 26:20.915
- Decent?
- Yeah.

26:24.151 --> 26:27.188
Brought you a little something,
a little housewarming, so to speak.

26:27.221 --> 26:30.357
- Floyd, this is completely unnecessary.
- Ah, don't worry about it.

26:30.391 --> 26:31.692
Open it up.

26:43.771 --> 26:44.872
There you go.

26:45.506 --> 26:47.174
Yeah, that's a fine robe.

26:50.945 --> 26:52.079
I don't know what to say.

26:53.247 --> 26:54.281
Nothing to say.

26:55.149 --> 26:56.150
You already thanked me.

26:59.420 --> 27:02.790
Well, thank you again. Really.

27:06.360 --> 27:07.861
All right. I'll leave you to it.

27:13.934 --> 27:15.169
It's good to have you here, pal.

27:56.577 --> 28:00.881
<i>I calculated quickly and figured
that it was very likely a suicide note.</i>

28:01.348 --> 28:02.449
<i>My suicide note.</i>

28:03.685 --> 28:05.386
<i>Of course, I had to assume
that the word "dome"</i>

28:05.919 --> 28:06.854
<i>was meant to be "done."</i>

28:07.554 --> 28:09.223
<i>It was a minor spelling error,</i>

28:09.256 --> 28:11.258
<i>and to be expected
under the circumstances.</i>

28:12.126 --> 28:13.861
<i>I had to forgive myself.</i>

28:42.890 --> 28:47.561
Um, I was never really a bathrobe guy before that.

28:48.429 --> 28:50.230
I've been a bathrobe
guy for ages.

28:50.531 --> 28:54.234
Used to steal them from hotels and...
uh, but now I can afford them.

28:55.336 --> 28:58.005
Barely.

28:58.038 --> 29:00.307
- How about you, Linda?
- I'm a woman, Dick.

29:00.341 --> 29:03.877
I would never have guessed that.

29:06.113 --> 29:07.247
Are we even getting paid
for this?

29:07.281 --> 29:10.351
Mm-mm.

29:10.384 --> 29:13.087
Okay, went off the rails
there for a bit. We're...

29:13.954 --> 29:15.089
Oh, yes.

29:16.256 --> 29:18.359
Floyd's life story.

29:18.392 --> 29:19.627
Right. Well, um...

29:21.562 --> 29:24.565
A few days had passed
before we got to work and

29:25.299 --> 29:27.334
I didn't really know
where to begin.

29:27.601 --> 29:32.139
But then I remembered reading Dmitry
Hardow's book on Francois Lip Shits,

29:32.506 --> 29:34.341
so I figured
I'd do the same thing.

29:34.609 --> 29:38.445
Just, uh, you know,
start interviewing him,

29:39.046 --> 29:41.982
ask him questions,
keep it relaxed and...

29:42.583 --> 29:45.052
...figure the rest
out from there.

29:46.120 --> 29:47.354
I should read the book.

29:57.231 --> 29:58.265
Why the French flag?

29:59.400 --> 30:02.102
Part French on my father's side
and part Indian too.

30:03.036 --> 30:04.071
Potawatomi.

30:05.472 --> 30:08.008
All the way back to the French-Indian
war on that side of the family.

30:11.111 --> 30:12.312
Napoleon?

30:17.719 --> 30:21.221
History has misjudged that man and
I can think of no greater tragedy.

30:21.689 --> 30:22.556
Hmm.

30:25.392 --> 30:27.327
The man's legacy... Hey.

30:28.061 --> 30:29.496
You should be recording this.

30:34.468 --> 30:37.971
Mmm, I haven't touched
this thing in years.

30:40.441 --> 30:43.611
- It's all yours.
- Micro Cassette.

30:47.615 --> 30:50.284
- Always wanted one of these.
- Knock yourself out.

30:54.354 --> 30:55.522
- Okay, let me have that.
- Oh...

30:55.556 --> 30:56.624
- I am sorry.
- Thank you very much.

30:56.658 --> 30:57.591
I didn't mean to, uh...

30:57.625 --> 30:58.559
Yeah, sorry.

30:58.592 --> 30:59.460
I'll change that out.

31:04.565 --> 31:05.599
Fresh take. There you go.

31:08.335 --> 31:10.738
Floyd, you've got a great voice.

31:11.706 --> 31:14.007
I used to be able to carry
a tune, but not anymore.

31:15.710 --> 31:17.377
Do you mind if I s... start?

31:18.245 --> 31:19.146
I'm an open book.

31:22.650 --> 31:27.054
Right, uh, before I do,
regarding the book.

31:27.488 --> 31:28.723
I have to ask.

31:31.626 --> 31:33.360
Why are you keeping it a secret?

31:34.161 --> 31:35.062
Hmm.

31:36.163 --> 31:37.364
It's a good question.

31:41.335 --> 31:44.338
We all live multicolored lives.

31:44.706 --> 31:47.609
Each and every one of us
and, uh...

31:49.510 --> 31:51.478
...we all have a range
of experiences.

31:53.146 --> 31:54.515
- And...
- You've been unfaithful.

31:58.185 --> 32:00.822
Let's not shit in the soup
just yet, my friend, okay?

32:00.855 --> 32:04.191
I mean, we're gonna pull some teeth but let's
try to ease into it a little bit, right?

32:04.224 --> 32:07.729
- Okay.
- For the record, I will say that my wife and I,

32:07.762 --> 32:12.299
we have a great relationship,
really terrific, uh...

