40:06.573 --> 40:07.274
Who is he?

40:08.242 --> 40:10.077
This is my father.

40:13.881 --> 40:14.915
Yes, indeed.

40:16.317 --> 40:19.220
This old cocksucker
is my dear old dad.

40:20.921 --> 40:22.323
Can he hear us?

40:22.356 --> 40:24.658
Can't hear a goddamn thing.
Can you, pops?

40:27.628 --> 40:28.595
This isn't right.

40:29.030 --> 40:31.699
Exactly. Exactly.

40:34.201 --> 40:36.070
Listen, I don't know
the pertinence on the decline

40:36.103 --> 40:38.773
of your relationship with your
father, and I'm not asking.

40:38.806 --> 40:41.876
I just want to let you know that you
can talk to me about anything any time,

40:41.909 --> 40:44.645
and there will never be
any judgment. Understood?

40:46.347 --> 40:49.150
As far as
this old bag of bones...

40:50.651 --> 40:51.485
...I hate him too.

40:52.219 --> 40:53.921
I just wish
he could hear me say that.

40:58.793 --> 41:00.795
Sometimes family
isn't family at all.

41:03.831 --> 41:05.833
Hey, why don't you, uh,
wait in the car?

41:05.866 --> 41:07.234
- I'll be right down, okay?
- Sure.

41:09.737 --> 41:11.138
- Hey, brother.
- What's up, Floyd?

41:11.672 --> 41:13.040
- Thanks for the help.
- Yeah, my pleasure.

41:13.074 --> 41:15.810
- Here's 20.
- Oh, you, uh, said 50.

41:16.911 --> 41:18.079
- Did I?
- Yeah.

41:19.080 --> 41:19.980
Okay.

41:20.948 --> 41:22.616
Of course I thought
it was his real father.

41:23.050 --> 41:25.219
I had no reason to believe
otherwise. And...

41:28.255 --> 41:29.924
...he got so emotional.

41:33.127 --> 41:34.028
I felt for him.

41:35.863 --> 41:37.298
And I knew he felt for me.

41:38.766 --> 41:40.067
He was coming from a good place.

41:41.902 --> 41:45.106
And he hadn't told you
yet what he did for a living?

41:49.310 --> 41:50.945
